http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Sivagiri-gets-a-reverent-visitor/article13998795.ece

Piety, peace and reverence for social reformer Sree Narayana Guru filled the air at Sivagiri Madhom on Wednesday as Vice President Hamid Ansari visited the pilgrimage centre at Varkala established by the Guru in early 20{+t}{+h}century.On his arrival on the premises by around 11.30 a.m., Mr. Ansari was received by the office-bearers of the Sree Narayana Dharma Sangham Trust including general secretary Swami Rhithambharananda, treasurer Swami Parananda, and Guru Dharma Pracharana Sabha secretary Swami Guruprasad.He interacted with Sree Narayana Dharma Sangham Trust president Swami Prakasananda during his visit.The Vice President, who was accompanied by Excise Minister K. Babu, Food and Civil Supplies Minister Anoop Jacob, Varkala Kahar, MLA, and District Collector Biju Prabhakar, was escorted to the ‘Maha Samadhi Mandiram’, the final resting place of the Guru to pay homage.He later inaugurated the newly laid granite stairway from the Saradha Madhom to the Maha Samadhi Mandiram, following which he paid obeisance at the Vaidika Madhom, where Sree Narayana Guru had lived and was visited by several prominent personalities including Mahatma Gandhi, Jawaharlal Nehru, B.R. Ambedkar, and Rabindranath Tagore.During his visit that lasted nearly half-an-hour, Mr. Ansari unveiled a plaque to mark the inauguration of the centenary celebrations of ‘Darsanamala’, written by Sree Narayana Guru; ‘Gurusthavam’, written by Malayalam poet Kumaran Asan on the occasion of the Guru’s 60{+t}{+h}birthday; and the proclamation of ‘I have no caste or no religion’ that had been made by the Guru in 1916.The new block of the Sivagiri Sree Narayana Senior Secondary School, Varkala, was also inaugurated by the Vice President.Mr. Ansari also planted a sapling of the ‘Elanji’ tree on the premises to mark his visit to the centre.The visit concluded by around 12 p.m. with the Vice President, waving at a large number of devotees who gathered at the pilgrim centre, as he was being escorted by the security personnel.